Whoa!

168
00:08:50,995 --> 00:08:52,617
Okay, all right, you get the point.

169
00:08:53,098 --> 00:08:53,598
Sorry, whoops.

170
00:08:54,459 --> 00:08:57,002
Let me go back, I got a little ahead of myself.

171
00:08:57,322 --> 00:08:58,123
Mario, quiet down.

172
00:08:58,464 --> 00:08:58,604
Okay.

173
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,221
This guy is ridiculous.

174
00:09:01,942 --> 00:09:02,562
What is that?

175
00:09:03,103 --> 00:09:06,227
The guy who defeated a fire-breathing dinosaur sounds like this?

176
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,190
Well, he does.

177
00:09:08,730 --> 00:09:09,511
Because he does.

178
00:09:10,072 --> 00:09:14,137
And suddenly we know an incredible amount about Super Mario's character.

179
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:16,078
He's a maniac.

180
00:09:16,498 --> 00:09:19,659
He is absolutely thrilled just to be alive,

181
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:21,740
whooping with every jump.

182
00:09:22,180 --> 00:09:24,241
He's never known true sadness,

183
00:09:24,501 --> 00:09:27,022
only surprise or temporary dismay,

184
00:09:27,082 --> 00:09:28,422
thanks to all the lives he's got,

185
00:09:28,782 --> 00:09:30,763
as he falls down a pit screaming.

186
00:09:30,783 --> 00:09:31,904
Whoa!

187
